    # Rochester's Geek Unconference

    BarCamp Rochester is an ad-hoc gathering born from the desire for people to share and learn in an open environment. Plan on a relaxed day of discussions, demos, and interaction from attendees. The spirit of BarCamp and unconferences in general, is that all attendees prepare a talk, and arrive ready to share. Regular talks are 20 minutes, Lightning Talks are 5 minutes.

    Presentations in the auditorium are recorded and streamed live. To be guaranteed a time slot in the auditorium, send your talk outline, slides, or idea to [talks@barcamproc.org](mailto:talks@barcamproc.org). All other presentations, including leftover slots in the auditorium, are scheduled the day of BarCamp.

    ### BarCamp Rochester, #{data.global.next_event}

    BarCamp Rochester will be held at the **[Rochester Institute of Technology](/directions/)** on **Saturday, #{data.global.next_date}**.

    ####Register by April 17th to reserve your free t-shirt and make sure we buy enough food!

    If you want to learn more about how BarCamp Rochester works, you can always check out [our How-To page](/howto/).

